{"key":"processedPost-11853332","value":{"id":11853332,"first":11852890,"last":11853451,"when":1263848392,"utime":"01/18/10 10:59 PM","content":"You mist ALL species from initiation through a few hours before harvest.&nbsp; Old advice not to mist after pins form was back in the early days when people were still using sealed up fruiting chambers.&nbsp; Wet pins would tend to rot or abort with no fresh air.&nbsp; Now that most people are using mini-greenhouses or shotgun terrariums for better performance, mist a few times daily to prevent the substrate from drying out.<br /><br />If a substrate in a tray is drying out, you can pour water directly around the edges of the tray, floating the substrate.&nbsp; Then, pour out any excess that didn't soak in, a few hours later.<br />RR","title":"Re: wutah i need some wutah","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}